                            <comment id="492355" author="paf0186" created="Thu, 2 Apr 2026 22:06:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for fs/lustre-release (master): &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65029&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65029&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20069&quot; title=&quot;osc: pass page index explicitly for DIO encrypt&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-20069&quot;&gt;LU-20069&lt;/a&gt; osc: pass page index explicitly for DIO encrypt&lt;br/&gt;
Patchset 3: pass cp_page_index explicitly to osc_encrypt_pagecache_blocks() for DIO, mirroring the decrypt path. Fixes compound page tweak mismatch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="492287" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 1 Apr 2026 19:42:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;Additional fix: also wrap filemap_get_folios_contig() for vvp_dev.c call site. The page cache iteration in ll_filemap_get_one_page_contig() uses this kernel function directly and can also receive large folios. Will add wrapper in compat layer to split these as well.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Superseded &amp;#8211; root cause was not readahead folios but compound pages from DIO allocator. See patchset 3 of 65029/65030.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
